# PauliBot System Diagrams

Based on GeeksforGeeks and Visual Paradigm UML standards, below are the Class Diagram / Entity Relationship Diagram and the Sequence Diagram of the PauliBot system.

## 1. Class Diagram / Entity Relationship Diagram

The Class Diagram illustrates the structure of the PauliBot system by showing its classes (models), attributes, methods, and relationships. It also serves as an Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD) showcasing database schema relationships.

```mermaid
classDiagram
    %% Django Built-in Models
    class AbstractUser {
        +String username
        +String password
        +String email
        +String first_name
        +String last_name
    }

    class CustomUser {
        +String student_id
        +Meta meta
        +__str__() String
    }

    class Conversation {
        +Integer id
        +Integer user_id
        +String title
        +DateTime created_at
        +DateTime updated_at
        +Boolean is_active
        +Meta meta
        +__str__() String
    }

    class ChatHistory {
        +Integer id
        +Integer user_id
        +Integer conversation_id
        +Text message
        +Text response
        +DateTime timestamp
        +Meta meta
        +__str__() String
    }

    class Location {
        +Integer id
        +String name
        +Text description
        +Boolean map_available
        +VectorField embedding
        +save()
        +__str__() String
    }

    class StaffMember {
        +Integer id
        +String name
        +String position
        +String office
        +VectorField embedding
        +save()
        +__str__() String
    }

    class FAQ {
        +Integer id
        +String category
        +String question
        +Text answer
        +VectorField embedding
        +save()
        +__str__() String
    }

    %% Inheritance
    AbstractUser <|-- CustomUser : extends

    %% Relationships
    CustomUser "1" -- "*" Conversation : owns (related_name='conversations')
    CustomUser "1" -- "*" ChatHistory : sends (related_name='chat_history')
    Conversation "1" -- "*" ChatHistory : contains (related_name='messages')
```

## 2. Sequence Diagram

The Sequence Diagram documents the process flow of a user sending a message to PauliBot and receiving a generative AI response powered by Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG).

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor User as Authenticated Student
    participant Frontend as View (chat_api)
    participant Logic as PauliBotLogic
    participant RAG as RAGSearcher
    participant DB as Vector Database
    participant Gemini as Gemini API (LLM)
    participant DjangoDB as PostgreSQL Database

    User->>Frontend: Send Message (POST /api/chat/)
    activate Frontend
    
    Frontend->>Logic: process_query(user_message)
    activate Logic
    
    Logic->>Logic: _build_context(user_message)
    activate Logic
    
    Logic->>RAG: search(query, limit=3)
    activate RAG
    
    RAG->>DB: Query Similar Vector Embeddings
    activate DB
    DB-->>RAG: Return Top Contexts (Locations, Staff, FAQs)
    deactivate DB
    
    RAG-->>Logic: Return Context Text
    deactivate RAG
    Logic-->>Logic: Format Context Prompt
    deactivate Logic
    
    Logic->>Gemini: generate_content(prompt)
    activate Gemini
    Gemini-->>Logic: Return AI Response String
    deactivate Gemini
    
    Logic-->>Frontend: Return AI Response
    deactivate Logic
    
    Frontend->>DjangoDB: get_or_create Conversation
    activate DjangoDB
    DjangoDB-->>Frontend: Return Conversation Instance
    deactivate DjangoDB
    
    Frontend->>DjangoDB: create ChatHistory(message, response)
    activate DjangoDB
    DjangoDB-->>Frontend: Save Confirmation
    deactivate DjangoDB
    
    Frontend-->>User: Return JSON Response with AI Message
    deactivate Frontend
```
